One of the presidential aspirants on the platform of Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) and Governor of Rivers State, Mr Nyesom Wilke, on Monday lamented that the ruling All Progressives Congress APC) has ruined the nation on all fronts. He stated this at the PDP secretariat at Allagbaka, Akure, the Ondo State capital while addressing delegates of the party. Wike, who was in the state to canvass the support of the party’s delegates ahead of the national convention of the party, noted that only a fearless personality could lead the nation in tackling the magnitude of challenges it’s currently facing. -Advertisement- He emphasised that since President Muhammadu Buhari took over the rein of the nation, a series of unfortunate incidents had started befalling the country. Changing the party’s delegates to vote for him at the convention, the two-term governor of Rivers State said: “I am here to make myself available to you that I want tun and win the presidential election of this country in 2023. I have a chance of winning the presidential election for the PDP. “Nigeria needs a fearless leader. Nigeria had never been divided like this as a country. No good news has come from the government of the APC. The only good news we have from APC is killings here, killings there every day. ” Let no one deceive you, for being a businessman does not make you be a good president. I started from the grassroots.” The state Chairman of PDP, Alhaji Fatai Adams declared that PDP remained that party that could fix the current socio-political and economic challenges APC had plunged the nation into. POLL He charged the electorate to vote for the candidates of the party across elective positions so that they could bring the nation out of the wood again.